verbose_text: X-gal staining of coronal sections of E12.5 Plag1 lacZ KI/+ (hereafter Plag1 KI/+; XREF_FIG G) and Plagl2 lacZ KI/+ (hereafter Plagl2 KI/+; XREF_FIG H) heterozygous brains revealed that lacZ had a similar distribution throughout the telencephalic VZ in both genotypes, again with apparently higher levels of lacZ expression in Plagl2 KI/+ cortices.
